1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,950
Most AI agent workflows

2
00:00:01,950 --> 00:00:03,900
trust what a model says it is.

3
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:05,850
Sol Ultra Gearbox verifies

4
00:00:05,850 --> 00:00:07,800
what actually ran. It routes Codex work

5
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,750
to typed Sol, Terra, and Luna roles.

6
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:11,700
Then it checks the real model,

7
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:13,650
reasoning effort, sandbox, lineage,

8
00:00:13,650 --> 00:00:15,600
token usage, and filesystem scope

9
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:17,550
from persisted runtime metadata.

10
00:00:17,550 --> 00:00:19,500
If anything is missing or mismatched,

11
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,450
it fails closed.

12
00:00:21,450 --> 00:00:23,400
The built-in doctor validates

13
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,350
six role profiles.

14
00:00:25,350 --> 00:00:27,300
Dry-run previews global changes,

15
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:29,250
while managed apply includes rollback.

16
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:31,200
This release passed twenty-three tests

17
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,150
and a six-role runtime smoke test.

18
00:00:33,150 --> 00:00:35,100
If your team needs multi-agent workflows

19
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:37,050
you can audit, reproduce,

20
00:00:37,050 --> 00:00:39,000
and reverse,

21
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,950
try Sol Ultra Gearbox

22
00:00:40,950 --> 00:00:42,900
on GitHub.

